OL,3,CThe train station frozen in time
OL,4,Cthat's now up for auction
OL,6,FOn the walls are old tin signs for
OL,7,Fproducts that, if they still exist,
OL,8,Fuse the internet to advertise these
OL,9,Fdays.
OL,11,FA porter's trolley, wheels slightly
OL,12,Frusted. Old station lamps which are
OL,13,Fnow hotels for insects.
OL,15,FThe railway track's still there,
OL,16,Fremarkably intact, but a whole world
OL,17,Fof wild flowers and the odd bramble
OL,18,Fhave claimed the sleepers for
OL,19,Fthemselves.
